Monkey Massacre

by: Sid Khandelwal

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I made this game because I think monkeys are funny animals and normally associated with eating bananas so the game and projectiles work. I also wanted to do a game thats was player vs player instead of single player so it could be more fun.

2. What I Learned

I learned that my game needed to have a shot reload time or else the game would be too easy because you could just spam all your shots and the game would be unplayable.

3. Architecture of My Game

The object manager class is the most important as it keeps track of what hits what, when something hits something, how many times something has been hit, etc. The other classes focus on smaller things that keep the game smooth and some classes are self explanatory based on their names like the monkey class and projectile class.

4. Technical Implementation

I am proud of how accurate the hit boxes of the monkeys and projectiles are. That part took a lot of trial and error, and required making visible hit boxes to manually change the width and height by minuscule amounts.

5. Most Challenging Part

The most challenging part of this game was adding all the visual effects like the background and the health. Finding a way to differentiate the monkeys and not ruin the game was difficult and eventually I added a thin border to the monkeys in their respective colors.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I would like to add a more animated version of the banana flying through the air and would like to add sound effects. A more interactive menu might also be better such as using arrow keys to select things instead of keyboard buttons.
